snippet.textDisplay:
I have a EVGA 2070 super black (dual fan, no RGB, no backplate), $480 USD before tax (a nice deal from Microcenter).
Slightly underclocked from XC ultras. OC'd slightly to match XC ultras just fine and can play modern titles averaging 70-80 frames MAX settings @1440P including CODMW, PUBG, and other heavy hitting titles. Linus is right about price performance ratio on the 2080 super. Almost not worth it for the extra +$200-$300.
These results paired with a AMD 3700X (stock clock, stock prism cooler) and cheap B450 tomahawk max motherboard, cheap 16gb gskill ripjaws 3200. Save $100 and get 3600X for the same gaming performance.
